<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="871" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 705.6358/8</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Swedish Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EWAF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ekengren</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">Department of Austro-</seg>
                                <lb/>
                                <seg rendition="#left">Hungarian Interests</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Minister of Sweden, representing Austro-Hungarian interests in
                                the United States, presents his compliments to his excellency the
                                Secretary of State and has the honor to inform him that
                                Austro-Hungarian <pb facs="0793" n="621" xml:id="pg_621"/> interests
                                in the Hawaiian Islands, which until recently have been in charge of
                                the Spanish Consul at Honolulu who has left, have been transferred
                                to the Royal Swedish Consulate at San Francisco, Calif.</p>
                            <p>The Minister of Sweden, therefore, begs to request his excellency the
                                Secretary of State to kindly inform the competent authorities of the
                                new jurisdiction of the Swedish Consulate in San Francisco.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <dateline rendition="#left">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-29"><hi rend="italic">October 29, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 31.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>